results.name: Jordan 12 Retro Royalty Taxi (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 12 Retro TD ‘Royalty’ delivers a simple two-tone colorway of the classic silhouette, featuring the same white and black color scheme of the OG ‘Taxi’ release from 1996. Stitched detailing radiates outward on the white leather upper, reinforced with contrasting black mudguards in a subtle lizard texture. A metallic gold Jumpman logo graces the tongue. A lightweight foam midsole is supported by an outsole equipped with herringbone-traction rubber pods under the forefoot and heel.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro Where the Wild Things Are (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 4 TD ‘Wild Things’ brings a winterized version of the classic silhouette to growing feet. The tan leather upper is updated with plush fleece construction on the collar and tongue. A quartet of individually colored eyelets are finished in neon green, pink, blue and red, with the latter two hues repeated on the sneaker’s mismatched wings. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and dark beige heel panel. The scaled-down build rides on a soft foam midsole, reinforced with grippy gum rubber under the forefoot and heel.

results.name: Jordan 3 Retro Pine Green (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro TD ‘Pine Green’ brings a refreshed colorway of the iconic silhouette to growing feet. The black nubuck upper is fortified with signature elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Contrasting green accents land on the perforated collar, cushy foam midsole and the Jumpman logo embroidered on the tongue. Additional Jumpman branding hits decorate the sneaker’s back heel and foam insole. Underfoot, the solid rubber outsole features a circular traction pattern for reliable grip.

results.name: Jordan 5 Retro Moonlight (2021) (TD)
results.story: The 2021 edition the Air Jordan 5 Retro TD ‘Oreo’ brings back a scaled-down version of a popular colorway first released in 2013. Like the original, the upper is constructed from black nubuck with translucent quarter panel netting. A silver Jumpman atop the tongue is complemented by a second Jumpman rendered in white embroidery on the back heel. The mid-top rides on a white foam midsole, embellished with speckled shark tooth detailing on the lateral sidewall.

results.name: Jordan 13 Retro White Obsidian Powder Blue (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro TD ‘Obsidian’ applies a familiar color palette to a condensed version of the classic silhouette originally released in 1997. The upper combines a navy leather base with tonal suede paneling and white leather overlays marked with circular stitch detailing. An embroidered Jumpman in powder blue decorates the tongue, while the 13’s holographic cat eye stands out on the lateral collar. Simplified tooling comes complete with rubber herringbone-traction pods underfoot.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Bordeaux (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro TD ‘Bordeaux’ updates the retro silhouette with a distinctive color combination lifted from an OG Air Jordan 7 release. Black and grey nubuck is utilized on the upper, featuring a patterned multicolor tongue directly inspired by the AJ7. Bordeaux accents enliven the sneaker’s throat and molded spoiler-like heel tab. A tonal Jumpman icon is embroidered on the back heel, complementing an amber-colored Jumpman on the rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro Lightning (2021) (TD)
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro TD ‘Lightning’ brings back a coveted 2006 colorway in scaled-down form. The mid-top carries a bright yellow nubuck upper with contrasting black netting on the quarter panel and throat. Dark grey accents make their way to the sneaker’s structural wings, interior tongue and rubber outsole. A white Jumpman icon is embroidered on the tongue, complementing a second Jumpman imprinted on the heel overlay. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a crisp white foam midsole.

results.name: Jordan 12 Retro Utility  (TD)
results.story: Offered in condensed sizing for a new generation of MJ fans, the Jordan 12 Utility TD ‘Grind’ delivers a stealthy colorway of the classic silhouette. The stitched upper is crafted from black tumbled leather with tonal overlays in smooth nubuck, replacing the 12’s typical lizard-texture leather. Atop the ballistic mesh tongue, a crimson Jumpman delivers a contrasting pop of color. The sneaker is mounted on a cushy foam midsole, supported underfoot by a speckled rubber outsole that incorporates 3% Nike Grind — recycled materials taken from manufacturing scraps and end-of-life footwear.

results.name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Pollen (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG TD ‘Pollen’ brings classic color blocking to a condensed version of the iconic silhouette made for little feet. The leather upper features a black base with yellow overlays and a matching yellow Swoosh. Additional branding hits include a woven Nike tag atop the tongue and a Wings logo stamped on the lateral collar flap. The two-tone design is offset by a crisp white midsole, supported underfoot by a grippy yellow rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Seafoam (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG TD ‘Seafoam’ treats the classic silhouette to a pastel makeover. The upper is crafted from pristine white leather with nubuck overlays in a pale green hue. Flat white laces are trimmed in Healing Orange for a contrasting pop of color. A woven Nike tag decorates the plush nylon tongue, which combines with a padded collar to deliver a comfortable fit. Underfoot, the solid rubber outsole features flex grooves and a concentric-circle traction pattern.

results.name: Jordan 3 Retro Racer Blue (TD)
results.story: Done up in classic color blocking, the Air Jordan 3 Retro TD ‘Racer Blue’ brings the iconic model to a new generation of Jordan die-hards. The upper is composed of tumbled white leather with dark grey elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Vibrant blue accents settle on the sneaker’s perforated collar, interior tongue and midsole, built with soft foam for a cushioned ride. Matching blue Jumpman branding decorates the tongue, sockliner and heel.

results.name: Jordan 13 Retro Low Very Berry (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro Low TD ‘Very Berry’ delivers a simplistic two-tone colorway of the sneaker that MJ wore between championships no. 5 and 6. This scaled down version features an upper constructed from a blend of black leather and synthetic suede, along with dimpled leather overlays in Very Berry. The distinctive red hue is repeated on the Jumpman logo that adorns the tongue and lateral collar. Underfoot, the outsole uses herringbone traction pods for sure footing.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro White Oreo (2021) (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 4 Retro TD ‘White Oreo’ applies a neutral palette to a condensed version of the classic silhouette made for little feet. The white leather upper retains the design hallmarks of the original, including structural wings and reinforced netting on the quarter panel and vamp. Light black speckling distinguishes the soft foam midsole in Tech Grey. Jumpman branding in a matching grey finish adorns the heel, while a contrasting red Jumpman stands out on the tongue.

results.name: Jordan 3 Retro A Ma Maniére (TD)
results.story: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 3 Retro SP TD ‘Raised By Women’ delivers a scaled-down version of the classic silhouette designed in collaboration with James Whitner’s luxury boutique. Inspired by the women in his life, Whitner dresses the shoe in tumbled white leather with grey suede overlays and quilted satin on the interior lining. Mismatched Jumpman and A Ma Maniére branding decorates each tongue, while ‘Nike Air’ is embossed on the yellowed heel tab. The same vintage tone is repeated on the foam midsole, contrasted by wraparound detailing in a dark violet hue.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Electric Green (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro TD ‘Electric Green’ showcases the same color blocking found on the iconic ‘Infrared’ colorway that Michael Jordan wore when he clinched his first NBA championship. This scaled-down version for little feet features a black nubuck build with a bright green Jumpman logo atop the tongue. The same vibrant hue is repeated on the spoiler-like heel tab and soft foam midsole. Underfoot, a rubber outsole offers durable traction.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Blue (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low TD ‘Legend Blue’ brings the OG colorway to a new generation of Jordan fans. Rendered in low-top form and scaled down to fit tiny feet, the vintage silhouette carries a white synthetic leather upper secured with elastic no-tie laces. An embroidered Jumpman adorns the mesh tongue in a familiar blue shade inspired by MJ’s alma mater. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Low Citrus (2021) (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low PS ‘Bright Citrus’ brings back a classic 2001 colorway in a condensed version designed for little feet. The low-top makes use of a white leather upper secured with no-tie elastic laces and reinforced with a tonal patent leather overlay. Bright orange Jumpman branding appears on the tongue and heel tab. The citrus hue makes a repeat appearance on the rubber outsole, featuring flex grooves and an oversized Jordan wordmark.

results.name: Jordan 1 Retro High Court Purple (TD) (2021)
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG TD ‘Court Purple’ delivers a two-tone colorway inspired by one of the OG ‘Metallic’ colorways from 1986. This scaled-down edition features a white leather upper with a signature Swoosh in a glossy violet finish. Matching purple branding hits take the form of a woven Nike tongue tag and a Jordan Wings logo stamped on the lateral collar. A satin-lined collar gives the shoe a polished look. The high-top is mounted a rubber cupsole, featuring the standard AJ1 traction pattern on the rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 13 Retro Gym Red Flint Grey (TD)
results.story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro TD ‘Red Flint’ delivers a scaled-down version of the iconic silhouette, rendered in color blocking that recalls the OG ‘Flint’ release from 1998. This pair discards the blue accents of the original, replacing them with a bold Gym Red finish on the interior tongue, collar lining and reflective mesh overlays. The rest of the upper pairs white leather with grey synthetic suede paneling that extends from the midfoot and around the heel. An embroidered Jumpman atop the tongue is joined by a second Jumpman icon within the sneaker’s holographic eye.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott British Khaki (TD)
results.story: The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro TD ‘British Khaki’ scales the down the collaborative release for a new generation of sneaker enthusiasts. The mid-top is outfitted in a tan suede upper with stash pouches on both sides of the collar. Bright Crimson accents make their way to Jumpman branding on the canvas tongue, along with mismatched Nike and Cactus Jack logos on each heel. The sneaker rides on a soft foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by a glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole.
